il search ,recent, favorites tabs (M365 Web App)","automationStatus":"Not Automated"}]},{"id":820079,"title":"Search: NLP search result does not render with specific search term (Locate the file uploaded by Renish)","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech","areaShort":"HighQ Tech","issueSource":"Internal","createdDate":"2025-02-28","description":"","functionality":"Upload","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/820079","tests":[]},{"id":823227,"title":"getMSV.action for on-prem should show as \"disabled\" or valid message and not \"not able to connect\"","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech","areaShort":"HighQ Tech","issueSource":"Internal","createdDate":"2025-03-17","description":"\u003cdiv>Not sure if defects are being tracked, so creating a bug as well.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr>\u003cspan style=\"display:inline !important;\">Refer to&nbsp;RITM4339720.\u003c/span>\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cspan style=\"box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(69, 84, 100);font-family:SourceSansPro, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:12px;text-align:left;display:inline !important;\">it is respective facet owner's responsibility to mark is as &quot;Disabled&quot; instead of showing not able to connect, which is not the right message on getMSV.action.\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003c/span>\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cspan style=\"display:inline !important;\">Not able to connect is misleading as modernization is by default not available for on-prem resources.\u003c/span>\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cspan style=\"display:inline !important;\">Please fix this at the earliest to avoid future confusions.\u003c/span>\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cspan style=\"display:inline !important;\">Thanks\u003c/span>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cbr>\u003cdiv>Defect link :&nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/823226\" tabindex=0 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;border-radius:2px;cursor:pointer;outline:transparent;text-decoration:underline;transition:color 80ms cubic-bezier(0.165, 0.84, 0.44, 1), background 80ms linear;\">Defect 823226\u003c/a>\u003cspan style=\"display:inline !important;\">: getMSV.action for on-prem should show as &quot;disabled&quot; or valid message and not &quot;not able to connect&quot;\u003cbr>\u003cbr>\u003cbr>This is important to be fixed so it doesnt affect synthetic monitors being setup.\u003c/span> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Infrastructure / Deployment","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/823227","tests":[]},{"id":823349,"title":"User sees module that they do not have access to","state":"Blocked","areaPath":"HighQ Tech","areaShort":"HighQ Tech","issueSource":"Internal","createdDate":"2025-03-18","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>Access the &quot;Gestión de Causas&quot; site using the user account &quot;Diego Vicchio.&quot; &gt;&gt; l\u003c/span>\u003cspan>ocate the &quot;New Cause&quot; module &gt;&gt; a\u003c/span>\u003cspan>ttempt to access the &quot;New Cause&quot; menu:\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cbr>\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>The system displays an error message.\u003c/span>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cbr>\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cb>This behavior is expected\u003c/b> because the client should not have access to the &quot;Nueva causa&quot; module, \u003cb>HOWEVER\u003c/b>,\n this module should not appear for this user just as the &quot;Seguimiento&quot;, \n&quot;Reportes&quot;, &quot;Tareas&quot;, and &quot;Agenda&quot; modules do not appear.\u003cbr>\u003cbr>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>System\nadministrator's view:\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cbr>\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cimg src=\"https://tr-legal