c/li>\n\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Severity:\u003c/strong> LOW \u003c/li>\n\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Type:\u003c/strong> Code \u003c/li>\n\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Score:\u003c/strong> 3.0/10 \u003c/li>\n\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Location:\u003c/strong> search-spring-app/src/main/java/com/highq/search/controller/IndexController.java, line 44 \u003c/li>\n\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Fixable:\u003c/strong> Yes \u003c/li>\n\u003cli>\u003cstrong>URL:\u003c/strong> \u003ca href=\"https://security.snyk.io/vuln/9e2f47db-3612-4d5c-a075-c987da8b1526\">https://security.snyk.io/vuln/9e2f47db-3612-4d5c-a075-c987da8b1526\u003c/a> \u003c/li>\n\u003c/ul>\n\n\u003ch2>Description \u003c/h2>\n\u003cp>Spring Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) \u003c/p>\n\n\u003ch2>AI-Generated Fix \u003c/h2>\n\u003ch3>Analysis \u003c/h3>\n\u003cp>The vulnerability is a Spring Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) issue. The controller endpoints are missing CSRF protection, making them vulnerable to CSRF attacks where malicious websites could trigger unauthorized requests on behalf of authenticated users. \u003c/p>\n\n\u003ch3>Explanation \u003c/h3>\n\u003cp>All POST and DELETE endpoints in the IndexController are vulnerable to CSRF attacks because they lack proper CSRF protection. The endpoints at lines 32, 37, 42, 47, and 52 can be exploited by malicious sites to perform unauthorized actions if a user is authenticated to the application. \u003c/p>\n\n\u003ch3>Recommended Fix \u003c/h3>\n\u003cpre>package com.highq.search.controller;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode;\nimport com.highq.search.index.service.ESIndexManagementService;\nimport com.highq.search.dto.MigrationDTO;\nimport com.highq.search.service.impl.IndexTemplateService;\nimport com.highq.search.service.impl.IsheetModuleService;\nimport com.highq.search.service.impl.MigrationService;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;\nimport lombok.extern.slf4j.Slf4j;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpHeaders;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.security.web.csrf.CsrfToken;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\nimport jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(&quot;/api&quot;)\n@Slf4j\n@RequiredArgsConstructor\npublic class IndexController {\n\n    private final IndexTemplateService templateService;\n    private final IsheetModuleService isheetModuleService;\n    private final MigrationService migrationService;\n    private final ESIndexManagementService esIndexManagementService;\n\n    @PostMapping(&quot;/index/migrateData&quot;)\n    public ResponseEntity migrateData(@RequestHeader HttpHeaders headers, @RequestBody @Valid MigrationDTO itemIdCsv, HttpServletRequest request) {\n        validateCsrfToken(request);\n        migrationService.runMigration(headers, itemIdCsv);\n        return new ResponseEntity&lt;&gt;(&quot;Migration task started&quot;, HttpStatus.OK);\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(&quot;/getIndexItemStatus&quot;)\n    public ResponseEntity&lt;Map&gt;&gt; getIndexItemStatus(@RequestHeader HttpHeaders headers, @RequestBody @Valid MigrationDTO itemIdCsv, HttpServletRequest request) {\n        validateCsrfToken(request);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(migrationService.getIndexItemStatus(itemIdCsv, headers.getFirst(&quot;X-TenantID&quot;)));\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(&quot;/indexTemplate&quot;)\n    public ResponseEntity setIndexTemplate(@RequestBody JsonNode indexTemplate, HttpServletRequest request) throws IOException {\n        validateCsrfToken(request);\n        templateService.addIndexTemplate(indexTemplate);\n        return new ResponseEntity&lt;&gt;(&quot;Index template was updated&quot;, HttpStatus.OK);\n    }\n\n    @DeleteMapping(&quot;isheetdeleteitems&quot;)\n    public void processIsheetDeleteItems(HttpServletRequest request) {\n        validateCsrfToken(request);\n        isheetModuleService.processIsheetDeleteColumnItems();\n    }\n\n    @DeleteMapping(&quot;/index/{id}&quot;)\n    public ResponseEntity deleteTenantData(@PathVariable String id, HttpServletRequest request) throws IOException {\n        validateCsrfToken(request);\n        log.info(&quot;Started delete indices for tenant from API call: {}&quot;, id);\n        JsonNode indices = esIndexManagementService.deleteTenantData(id);\n        return new ResponseEntity&lt;&gt;(indices, HttpStatus.OK);\n    }\n\n    private void validateCsrfToken(HttpServletRequest request) {\n        CsrfToken csrfToken = (CsrfToken) request.getAttribute(CsrfToken.class.getName());\n        if (csrfToken != null) {\n            String headerToken = request.getHeader(csrfToken.getHeaderName());\n            String parameterToken = request.getParameter(csrfToken.getParameterName());\n            \n            if (headerToken == null &amp;&amp; parameterToken == null) {\n                throw new SecurityException(&quot;CSRF token is required&quot;);\n            }\n            \n            String actualToken = headerToken != null ? headerToken : parameterToken;\n            if (!csrfToken.getToken().equals(actualToken)) {\n                throw new SecurityException(&quot;Invalid CSRF token&quot;);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\u003c/pre>\n\n\u003ch3>Security Rationale \u003c/h3>\n\u003cp>The fix adds CSRF token validation to all state-changing endpoints (POST and DELETE). Each endpoint now validates the CSRF token by checking if it matches the expected token from the session. This prevents unauthorized cross-site requests from being executed, as attackers cannot obtain the valid CSRF token from a different origin due to the same-origin policy. \u003c/p>\n\n\u003ch3>Implementation Steps \u003c/h3>\n\u003col>\n\u003cli>Step 1: Apply the fix to IndexController.java - add HttpServletRequest parameter to all POST/DELETE endpoints and call validateCsrfToken() \u003c/li>\n\u003cli>Step 2: Add the validateCsrfToken() helper method that checks for valid CSRF tokens \u003c/li>\n\u003cli>Step 3: Ensure Spring Security is configured with CSRF protection enabled (default behavior) \u003c/li>\n\u003cli>Step 4: Update client-side code to include CSRF tokens in requests via headers or form parameters \u003c/li>\n\u003cli>Step 5: Test all endpoints to ensure CSRF protection is working correctly \u003c/li>\n\u003cli>Step 6: Consider implementing proper API authentication (JWT tokens) for REST APIs as an alternative to CSRF protection \u003c/li>\n\u003c/ol>","functionality":"Security / Vulnerabilities","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/880582","tests":[]},{"id":882578,"title":"Dataviz : No Data After Pie Chart Drill Down","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech","areaShort":"HighQ Tech","issueSource":"Internal","createdDate":"2025-10-26","description":"\u003cdiv>Test case:&nbsp; 225839 || CD31866 Verification of drill down from Multi-iSheet source in Wiki module \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>Refer attached screen recording for better understanding of error. \u003c/div>","functionality":"DataViz / Charts / Dashboard","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/882578","tests":[{"id":225839,"title":"To check drill down from Multi-iSheet source in Wiki module.","automationStatus":"Automated-UI"}]},{"id":885129,"title":"Files | Files are not rendered on Index page when any view is seleted (Custom / Default)","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech","areaShort":"HighQ Tech","issueSource":"Internal","createdDate":"2025-11-05","description":"","functionality":"Files / Documents","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/885129","tests":[]},{"id":890169,"title":"[Legacy] Search Action dropdown missing post NLP search in Isheet","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech","areaShort":"HighQ Tech","issueSource":"Automation","createdDate":"2025-11-20","description":"\u003c