ueSource":"Scrum QA","createdDate":"2024-09-09","description":"\u003cspan>Test environment:\u003cbr>\u003c/span>\u003cdiv>t=5.8.14-alpha.2998_dav_2024_09_09_14_47_41_lcbr_4ad0527\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>Branch name = feature-dav-improvements\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cb>Scenario 1:\u003c/b> Those filter also appears as a filter item which are not existing in a DMD isheet.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cb>Pre-condition:\u003c/b>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cul>\u003cli>DMD isheets must be created in 2 different sites. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cul>\u003cli>Files with different status must be existing in both of the site. (Checked out, e-Signature related status, Allocate for review related status, Contract express related status) \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cul>\u003cli>Create a multi-isheet source adding DMD isheets from both of the sites &amp; add all different columns of DMD isheet in the source. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cb>Steps:\u003c/b>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>1. Login through sytem admin user.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>2. In a Home dashboard, configure a chart for multi-isheet source which consists of DMD isheets (selecting File status on Category)\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>3. Now Go to Site admin &gt;&gt; Files, Disable &quot;Enable document review workflow&quot; in both of the sites in which DMD isheet is created.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>4. Again Go to Home dashboard &gt;&gt; Verify configured chart for multi-isheet source. (Status related to document review workflow will not appear in the configured chart)\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>5. Edit the configured chart &amp; select File status column on Filter &gt;&gt; Verify filter items.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cb>Actual Result:\u003c/b>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cul>\u003cli>Status related to document review workflow appears in the configured chart even if those status do not appear in a DMD isheet. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cb>Expected Result:\u003c/b>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cul>\u003cli>Those status should only appear as a filter items which are available in the DMD isheets. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cb style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Scenario 2:\u003c/b>\u003cspan>&nbsp;Status from TMD isheet do not fetch if a multi-isheet source consists of DMD + TMD iSheet.\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cb style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Pre-condition:\u003c/b>\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;padding:0px 0px 0px 40px;\">\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">DMD &amp; TMD isheets must be created in a site. \u003c/li>\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Files with different status must be existing in the site. (Checked out, e-Signature related status, Allocate for review related status, Contract express related status) \u003c/li>\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Tasks with different status, priority must be created in a site. \u003c/li>\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Create a multi-isheet source adding DMD &amp; TMD isheets in it. (From DMD isheet select &quot;File status&quot; column &amp; in a below added TMD isheet select &quot;Priority&quot; or &quot;List&quot;) \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cb style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Steps:\u003c/b>\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">1. Login through sytem admin user.\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">2. In a Home dashboard, configure a chart for multi-isheet source which consists of DMD + TMD isheets.\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">3. Select a column on Category in which &quot;File status&quot; exist, any column on Value &amp; preview the chart. \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">4. Select the same column on Filter which is selected on Category &amp; verify the filter items.\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cb style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Actual Result:\u003c/b>\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;padding:0px 0px 0px 40px;\">\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Filter items from DMD isheet is only available whereas filter items from TMD isheets are not fetched in the filter menu. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cb style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Expected Result:\u003c/b>\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;padding:0px 0px 0px 40px;\">\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Items from all different isheets of the multi-isheet source should be available in the filter menu. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/div> \u003c/div> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>Note:\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>Issue exist for UDB dashboard as well.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cspan>Find attached video for reference.\u003cbr>\u003c/span>\u003cbr>","functionality":"DataViz / Charts / Dashboard","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/785344","tests":[]},{"id":785849,"title":"DataViz : When hide empty section prop