m SDHQ.&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003cspan>Attempts to execute the performance query showed an excessive number of connections.&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003cspan>Actions were taken to terminate the blocking sessions, but the issue persists.\u003c/span> \u003c/li>\u003cli>Enclosed are the results of the performance query taken at different times, indicating high CPU utilization and a large volume of queries, which are contributing to the delayed query responses. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul>\u003cdiv>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9);\">\u003cspan style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">After investigating the situation through Splunk Logs, I noted that the execution time of the below two stored procedures was max.&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9);\">\u003cspan style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">This led to the database connection becoming unavailable, and consequently, a &quot;maximum connection limit reached&quot; error was reported for the sdhq instance.\u003c/span>\u003cspan style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9);\">\u003cul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;padding:0px 0px 0px 20px;\">\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Griffin_sheet_getSheetAlertersActivity\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/li>\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Griffin_sheet_initiateContractItemProcessing \u003c/li> \u003c/ul>\u003cdiv>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>I request iSheet Team to investigate the highlighted scenario and share/update solutions to prevent these SPs from blocking database connections in the future, if any!\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Splunk Logs \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;padding:0px 0px 0px 4