date the value of it system not throws a validation message &quot;Start Date / Due date cannot be updated when task has dependency&quot; instead of this system gives 200 but not updated the value.\u003cspan style=\"font-size:12px;text-align:left;display:inline !important;\">\u003c/span> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Tasks / Task Manager","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/742280","tests":[{"id":229421,"title":"CD-35762 Verify that the update item api request does not update the Start/Due date column values for dependant tasks.","automationStatus":"TBD"}]},{"id":742298,"title":"isheet modernisation - Metadata view applied in task module does not give result when user does not have list access but is assignee to some of the tasks in list","state":"Blocked","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\COL\\COL-Task_Event_QA","areaShort":"COL / COL-Task_Event_QA","issueSource":"Regression QA","createdDate":"2024-03-01","description":"\u003cdiv>Steps:\u003cbr>\u003cspan style=\"\">1) Task module should be enabled in site.&nbsp;\u003cbr>2) Create one TMD sheet and apply view of TMD in task settings\u003cbr>\u003c/span>2) Some list should be created for task module (List 1 , List 2)\u003cbr>3) Add one normal user to site. Normal user should have access to above mentioned task lists\u003cbr>4) Now login with system admin user and add some tasks in the mentioned lists. Those tasks should be assigned to normal user who does not have access to these task list\u003cbr>\u003cbr>Now login with normal user and click on task module. User is not able to see the tasks in which user is assignee\u003cbr>\u003cbr>\u003cbr>Note : Root cause of problem is task module is sending limit as INTEGER.MAX_LIMIT which cannot be consumed by elastic search. In normal case where user has access to task list from task module itemids are getting sent so we are able to get the size using itemids length. But in this case where there are no itemids and limit is int max value it is not possible to make a bifurcation\u003cbr>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"iSheet","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/742298","tests":[]},{"id":746365,"title":"Order by \"\"Desc\" not working as expected for Get all tasks API ","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\COL\\COL-Task_Event_QA","areaShort":"COL / COL-Task_Event_QA","issueSource":"Regression QA","createdDate":"2024-03-27","description":"\u003cdiv>Order by &quot;&quot;Desc&quot; not working as expected for Get all tasks API \u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Tasks / Task Manager","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/746365","tests":[]},{"id":749381,"title":"Guiding text in assignee field is not complete when user Add task from File module","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\COL\\COL-Task_Event_QA","areaShort":"COL / COL-Task_Event_QA","issueSource":"Scrum QA","createdDate":"2024-04-17","description":"\u003cdiv>Assignee field has the guiding text as &quot;Seach a&quot; alone. Complete sentence is not visible in Add task window if user tries to add task from File module. \u003c/div>","functionality":"Tasks / Task Manager","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/749381","tests":[]},{"id":765583,"title":"Tasks: When editing a list in any Task, the 'Save' and 'Discard' buttons are covering the 'Add New List' link","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\COL\\COL-Task_Event_QA","areaShort":"COL / COL-Task_Event_QA","issueSource":"UAT","createdDate":"2024-06-06","description":"\u003cdiv>When editing a list from the dropdown menu in any Task, the 'Save' and 'Discard' buttons are covering the 'Add New List' link, making it inaccessible. \u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cp>Steps to Reproduce: \u003c/p>\u003col>\u003cli>Click on any Task in Task module. \u003c/li>\u003cli>Navigate to the list editing feature. \u003c/li>\u003cli>Observe that the 'Save' and 'Discard'