SQ4","areaShort":"Core / HQ-Core-SQ4","issueSource":"Scrum QA","createdDate":"2024-08-08","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>Test environment:\u003cbr>\u003c/span>\u003cdiv>t=5.8.10-alpha.2948_collabscrum35_2024_08_08_16_27_47_lcbr_a7d4893\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>Branch name = feature-custompages-bugfixing\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>Pre-condition:\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cspan>- From System vocabulary page update name of &quot;Custom Pages&quot; &amp; &quot;Home&quot; as &quot;Custom Pages 123&quot;, &quot;Home 123&quot;\u003c/span>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"DataViz / Charts / Dashboard","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/778779","tests":[]},{"id":809553,"title":"Enumeration Attack on Server's Directories","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\Core\\HQ-Core-SQ4","areaShort":"Core / HQ-Core-SQ4","issueSource":"UAT","createdDate":"2025-01-03","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>We discovered that the HighQ application is vulnerable to a directory enumeration attack. We were able to enumerate \u003cbr>\u003c/span>\u003cdiv>existing directories within the web server because the web server responded with different messages based on the \u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cspan>validity of the directory names\u003c/span>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Other","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/809553","tests":[]},{"id":809557,"title":"Lack of Session Timeout Mechanism Allows Identity Theft","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\Core\\HQ-Core-SQ4","areaShort":"Core / HQ-Core-SQ4","issueSource":"Internal","createdDate":"2025-01-03","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>After performing a successful authentication in the application, a session starts between the user’s browser and the \u003cbr>\u003c/span>\u003cdiv>application. The user is identified through a session identifier, which is stored in the application’s servers, and within the \u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>cookie stored in the user’s browser. As long as the session is active, accessing the application using the session \u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>identifier, which was generated by the application and given to the user, allows the application to identify the specific \u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>user.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>The application does not implement a session timeout mechanism, thus allowing sessions that are idle for more than 1 \u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>hour to remain active. As a result, an attacker with physical or remote access to the victim’s machine can use an open \u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>inactive browser, which was previously used to access the application and fully impersonate application users.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cspan>The attack’s success relies on the condition that the user did not perform a successful logout from the application.\u003c/span>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Performance / Slowness","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/809557","tests":[]},{"id":814493,"title":"Title tag value gets removed for Custom page and System dashboard CK source if title tag creates under SVG tag.","state":"Approved","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\Core\\HQ-Core-SQ4","areaShort":"Core / HQ-Core-SQ4","issueSource":"Scrum QA","createdDate":"2025-02-03","description":"","functionality":"DataViz / Charts / Dashboard","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/814493","tests":[]},{"id":816886,"title":"Dataviz: Wrong Chart Shown for isheet [Enable iSheet API for DataViz as TRUE]","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\Core\\HQ-Core-SQ4","areaShort":"Core / HQ-Core-SQ4","issueSource":"Automation","createdDate":"2025-02-13","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003ctable style=\"box-sizing:border-box;border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0px;margin:0px;max-width:100%;background-color:rgb(252, 252, 252);table-layout:fixed;color:rgb(64, 64, 64);fon