"id":899881,"title":"Template import does not respect module disable state: Home re-enabled while Custom Page remains disabled","state":"New","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\Core\\HQ-Core-SQ4","areaShort":"Core / HQ-Core-SQ4","issueSource":"Scrum QA","createdDate":"2026-01-12","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cdiv style=\"font-family:'Segoe UI';\">\u003cp>After creating a site, adding a \u003cstrong>Home\u003c/strong> page and a \u003cstrong>Custom Page (CP)\u003c/strong>, saving the site as a template, \u003cstrong>disabling Home via ASP Config\u003c/strong>, importing the template in the \u003cstrong>same instance\u003c/strong>, and then \u003cstrong>re-enabling Home via ASP Config\u003c/strong>, the \u003cstrong>Modules\u003c/strong> state is inconsistent: \u003c/p>\u003cul>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Expected:\u003c/strong> Both \u003cstrong>Home\u003c/strong> and \u003cstrong>Custom Page\u003c/strong> should appear \u003cstrong>Disabled\u003c/strong> in \u003cstrong>Site Admin → Modules\u003c/strong> (consistent with pre-import ASP config state carried by template). \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Actual:\u003c/strong> \u003cstrong>Home\u003c/strong> shows \u003cstrong>Enabled\u003c/strong>, while \u003cstrong>Custom Page\u003c/strong> shows \u003cstrong>Disabled\u003c/strong>. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul>\u003cp>This indicates the template import and/or ASP Config re-enable logic is selectively re-enabling Home but not applying consistent module state across pages. \u003c/p> \u003c/div>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"DataViz / Charts / Dashboard","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/899881","tests":[]},{"id":901457,"title":"TR logo missing on login screen when authenticating via API‑registered applications (Client ID & Secret Key flow) also additional \"test\" word is coming in title","state":"Blocked","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\Core\\HQ-Core-SQ4","areaShort":"Core / HQ-Core-SQ4","issueSource":"Scrum QA","createdDate":"2026-01-20","description":"\u0