atedDate":"2026-03-13","description":"\u003ch2>TSI Reference \u003c/h2>\u003cp>TSI: \u003ca href=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/913137\">#913137 – Case 23075352 – Serious New File Download Issue – Cloudflare – Procopio\u003c/a> \u003c/p>\u003ch2>Issue Summary \u003c/h2>\u003cp>Following the \u003cstrong>iSheet modernization migration\u003c/strong> of \u003cstrong>Procopio, Cory, Hargreaves &amp; Savitch LLP\u003c/strong>, the document download API endpoint started behaving incorrectly. \u003c/p>\u003ch3>Two-phase issue: \u003c/h3>\u003col>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Phase 1 (Resolved by Cloudflare config change):\u003c/strong> API was returning an HTML file with a \u003cstrong>Cloudflare 504 Gateway Timeout\u003c/strong> error instead of the expected PDF file. \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Phase 2 (Still Active):\u003c/strong> After the Cloudflare fix, the API now returns the file but with a \u003cstrong>gibberish/unrecognizable filename\u003c/strong> and \u003cstrong>wrong file type\u003c/strong>. The file downloads with an unknown extension — renaming to \u003ccode>.pdf\u003c/code> doesn’t open it, but renaming to \u003ccode>.eml\u003c/code> opens it, meaning the API is returning an email-type file instead of the PDF. \u003c/li> \u003c/ol>\u003ch3>Key Details \u003c/h3>\u003cul>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Instance:\u003c/strong> dealroom.procopio.com/procopio \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Module:\u003c/strong> Document Resource API / File Download \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Affected User:\u003c/strong> morgan.newman@procopio.com \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Issue first reported:\u003c/strong> March 9, 2026 at 11:58 PM UTC \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Cloudflare error observed:\u003c/strong> March 10, 2026 at 00:44 UTC \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>Secondary issue reported:\u003c/strong> March 10, 2026 at 11:31 AM (client local time) \u003c/li>\u003cli>Support has \u003cstrong>replicated the issue\u003c/strong> on the client instance. \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003cstrong>NOTE:\u003c/strong> This instance was recently modernized and these errors did not occur before modernization. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul>\u003ch2>Investigation Goals \u003c/h2>\u003col>\u003cli>Identify why the document download API is returning an \u003ccode>.eml\u003c/code> (email) file instead of the original PDF post-modernization. \u003c/li>\u003cli>Determine if the incorrect Content-Type or response header is being set in the modernized file download path. \u003c/li>\u003cli>Investigate if the file store migration incorrectly stored or mapped the file type/metadata for this instance. \u003c/li>\u003cli>Check if this is related to the previously reported TSI #911707 (iSheet attachment 403 issue) — both from Procopio post-modernization. \u003c/li>\u003cli>Assess if other modernized instances could be affected by the same file download issue. \u003c/li>\u003cli>Provide a fix to restore correct file download behaviour (correct filename, correct file type). \u003c/li> \u003c/ol>","functionality":"Download","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/913473","tests":[]},{"id":913665,"title":"system error when editing isheet record","state":"Pending Validation","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\SWAT","areaShort":"SWAT","issueSource":"Production","createdDate":"2026-03-13","description":"\u003cdiv>users are getting system error while trying to edit the isheet record. \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>after investigation I found duplicate entry in&nbsp;\u003cspan>metadata.gfn_sheetItemLock table for the record user is trying to edit.\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cbr>\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>we need to provide update script to delete one duplicate entry and also need to investigate the cause of the issue. \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cbr>\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>currently we have two client facing same issue, details are below.\u003c/span> \u003c/d