rmittent. We cannot reliably replicate it on local environments or client instances. No specific pattern has been identified. \u003c/li>\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cstrong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">Logs:\u003c/strong>\u003cspan>&nbsp;\u003c/span>In most cases, there are no related errors or exceptions captured in Datadog. still I have downloadded logs for the one of the instances. \u003c/li>\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cstrong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">Error Messages:\u003c/strong>\u003cspan>&nbsp;\u003c/span>In a few instances, a &quot;batch is changed&quot; (or related batch ID) message/error has been observed. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul>\u003cp style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 16px;text-wrap:wrap;font-size:16px;font-feature-settings:&quot;tnum&quot;;color:rgb(33, 34, 35);font-family:Clario, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">\u003cstrong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">\u003ch3 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0.5em;font-weight:500 !important;font-size:28px !important;font-family:Clario-medium, Clario, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif  !important;font-size-adjust:none !important;font-feature-settings:normal  !important;\">\u003cstrong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">Engineering Investigation Tasks\u003c/strong> \u003c/h3>\u003cbr>1. &quot;Batch ID does not exist&quot; / Batch Changed Issue\u003c/strong> \u003c/p>\u003cul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1em;color:rgb(33, 34, 35);font-family:Clario, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;\">\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Investigate the application logs and code path for the &quot;batch is changed&quot; or missing Batch ID scenarios. \u003c/li>\u003cli style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Determine why batch synchronization is failing or losing context during the signing lifecycle. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul>\u003cp sty