v>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"iSheet","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916053","tests":[]},{"id":916109,"title":"Unable to export 84k records from a metadata iSheet","state":"Active","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\SWAT","areaShort":"SWAT","issueSource":"Production","createdDate":"2026-03-30","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cspan> \u003cspan dir=ltr> \u003cul> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Customer Name: City of Philadelphia\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Affected site(s): (URL or at least siteID)&nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://philalaw.highq.com/philalaw/sheetHome.action?metaData.siteID=117&amp;metaData.parentFolderID=0&amp;metaData.sheetId=313&amp;indexPage=true&amp;forcelyGridOpen=false&amp;modalCounter=\">https://philalaw.highq.com/philalaw/sheetHome.action?metaData.siteID=117&amp;metaData.parentFolderID=0&amp;metaData.sheetId=313&amp;indexPage=true&amp;forcelyGridOpen=false&amp;modalCounter=\u003c/a>\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Permission to enter: (Yes/No) Yes\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Description\n of the issue: (no one line descriptions unless the issue is a one line \ndescription) Client is trying to export a Metadata iSheet with 84k \nrecords, however, it is only exporting 10k\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Module(s) Affected: iSheet\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cspan>- if affected module is Workflow, provide WF details and WF Audit (Yes/No)&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Number of Users Affected: All\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Specific users affected: (email/userID)&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Approximate date and time stamps when the issue occurred for the user(s) specified:&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Event visible in Data Dog (Yes/No): if yes - URL:&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Event visible in DataDog (Yes/No): if yes - URL:&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Managed to replicate the issue: (Yes/No) Yes, in Client instance\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cspan>- if yes, where? (local UAT/Client instance/both)&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Troubleshooting\n steps taken by Support so far: logged into the site (SiteID=117), tried\n to export the iSheet (iSheetId=313) in different formats, also as an \nimport template and only 10k of the 84k records were exported.\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Screenshots: (Yes/No)&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Video of the issue: (Yes/No)&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>HAR file: (Yes/No)&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Site Template: (Yes/No)&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Permission to take non-obfuscated database backup: (Yes/No)&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:0px;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>Client’s initial description copied from Support ticket:&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/span> \u003c/span>\u003cspan style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:14.6667px;display:inline !important;\">We\n are trying to export a csv for the file metadata iSheet but we can only\n get 10,000 records.&nbsp; How do we get all 84,000 rows in the .csv file?&nbsp; \nCan you generate the file for us or recommend a way that we can generate\n a full document?\u003c/span>\u003cbr>\u003cbr>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Export","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916109","tests":[]},{"id":916213,"title":"Investigation >> Smart folder not fetching a files","state":"Active","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\SWAT","areaShort":"SWAT","issueSource":"Production","createdDate":"2026-03-30","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cb>Issue description:\u003c/b>&nbsp;The customer has a \u003cstrong>smart folder\u003c/strong> configured with the rule \u003cstrong>“Sample Forms = Yes”\u003c/strong>, and documents matching this rule should be visible in the smart folder. However, due to an issue, the expected documents are not appearing.\u003cdiv style=\"font-family:'Segoe UI';\">\u003cp>I discussed this issue with \u003cstrong>\u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,7e0d44de-7aef-64f6-8cf7-0535fa739d52\">@Donis, Jorge (Operations &amp; Technology)\u003c/a> \u003c/strong>. To validate the behavior, we created a \u003cstrong>new smart folder with the same rule\u003c/strong>&nbsp;and observed the \u003cstrong>same result\u003c/strong>.So I believe there is some issue with data specific. \u003c/p> \u003c/div> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cimg src=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/66e74794-9916-410b-b624-07d49748bbff/_apis/wit/attachments/394f4b7e-4b59-4214-ace4-e8e4b69b8cdb?fileName=image.png\" alt=Image>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cul>\u003cli>\u003cdiv style=\"font-family:'Segoe UI';\">\u003cp>I have taken a \u003cstrong>database backup on the India server\u003c/strong>. As you are aware, this instance is currently in the \u003cstrong>Modernization\u003c/strong> phase, and there is \u003cstrong>no modernization setup configured on the India server\u003c/strong> at this time. We will need to \u003cstrong>configure all the required microservices first\u003c/strong>. Only after completing this setup will we be able to \u003cstrong>access the instance successfully\u003c/strong>. \u003c/p> \u003c/div> \u003c/li>\u003cli>As discussed with \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,7dd6744d-0b46-67bd-adbe-68611c21ddbd\">@Lodhari, Alpesh K. (Operations &amp; Technology)\u003c/a>, I have raised this ADO ticket. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Files / Documents","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916213","tests":[]},{"id":916217,"title":"Wijmo drill-down fails to load data when the Chart filter value contains single quote (')","state":"Active","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\SWAT","areaShort":"SWAT","issueSource":"Production","createdDate":"2026-03-30","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>When a drill-down is opened with a filter value containing a single quote ('), the Wijmo grid fails to load data due to inconsistent encoding handling in the drill-down to Wijmo flow.\u003cbr>\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>The client reported this with Choice Column values in Pie and Line Chart filters, but the issue is not limited to a specific column type or chart type — it reproduces with any filter value containing a single quote.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cspan>The issue has been reproduced in both the client's environment and the \u003ca href=\"https://supportuatv4.highq.com/supportuatvfour/\">supportuatvfour\u003c/a> instance using local data.&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cbr>\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cb>Note:\u003c/b> This works correctly in the Legacy iSheet View (non-Wijmo grid).\u003cbr>\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cbr>\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>Please refer to the attached snapshots for details.\u003c/span>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cul>\u003cli>\u003cimg src=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/66e74794-9916-410b-b624-07d49748bbff/_apis/wit/attachments/970e3bb8-baa4-43ed-b9c1-300b96603b11?fileName=image.png\" alt=Image style=\"width:139px;\" width=139 height=87>&nbsp;&nbsp;\u003cimg src=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/66e74794-9916-410b-b624-07d49748bbff/_apis/wit/attachments/3074c51d-53fa-427f-99b9-a7dd983fdaa6?fileName=image.png\" alt=Image style=\"width:234px;\" width=234 height=84> \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003ca href=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/66e74794-9916-410b-b624-07d49748bbff/_apis/wit/attachments/48801e67-d4a9-444c-8b92-0d42d1306269?fileName=single-quote-doesnot-work-with-wizmo.har&amp;download=true\" tabindex=0 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(0, 90, 158);border-radius:2px;cursor:pointer;outline:transparent;text-decoration:underline;transition:color 80ms cubic-bezier(0.165, 0.84, 0.44, 1), background 80ms linear;\">single-quote-doesnot-work-with-wizmo.har\u003c/a>\u003cbr> \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003ca href=\"https://supportuatv4.highq.com/supportuatvfour/siteHomePage.action?metaData.siteID=3370&amp;metaData.homePageID=9617\">Imported Site Template and Data\u003c/a> \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>Requesting the development team to review the issue, my findings and provide a fix.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>My Investigation: \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cul>\u003cli>\u003cspan>This does \u003cspan style=\"display:inline !important;\">not&nbsp;\u003c/span>appear a metadata loading issue.\u003c/span> \u003c/li>\u003cli>The metadata and bootstrap API calls return 200, but the grid data does not load when the filter value contains a single quote. \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003ca href=\"http://single-quote-doesnot-work-with-wizmo.har\">Observations from HAR\u003c/a> \u003c/li>\u003cul>\u003cli>Drill-down URL contains: filterValue_712035_1=Project%27s \u003c/li>\u003cli>showIsheetTopPage.action sends the same value as: filterValue_712035_1=Project%27s \u003c/li>\u003cli>isheetGridV2.action returns the filter in searchDataXML as:&nbsp;\u003cspan>Project's\u003c/span> \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/ul>Root cause appears to be improper escaping of single quote during encoding/decoding in the drill-down to Wijmo filter flow, which causes the grid data load to fail.\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cul>\u003cli>The drill-down URL already contains an encoded apostrophe: \u003c/li>\u003cul>\u003cli>The page is opened with: ...sheetHome.action?...&amp;filterValue_712035_1=Project%27s&amp;... \u003c/li>\u003cli>So the original filter value is: Project's \u003c/li>\u003cli>but in the request URL it is already percent-encoded as: Project%27s \u003c/li> \u003c/ul>\u003cli>The same encoded value is posted again in form data: \u003c/li>\u003cul>\u003cli>In showIsheetTopPage.action, the POST body contains: filterValue_712035_1=Project%27s \u003c/li>\u003cli>The application is sending an already URL-encoded value (Project%27s) as form data instead of the raw value (Project's), which is a classic double-encoding issue. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul>\u003cli>Server later converts it back to Project's \u003c/li>\u003cul>\u003cli>In the response from isheetGridV2.action: searchDataXML&quot;:&quot;...&lt;![CDATA[Project's]]&gt;...&quot; \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/ul> \u003c/div>","functionality":"iSheet","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916217","tests":[]},{"id":916282,"title":"searching for keywords in PDF's do not display document content \"preview\"","state":"Approved","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\SWAT","areaShort":"SWAT","issueSource":"Production","createdDate":"2026-03-30","description":"\u003cdiv>Search for any keywords from search and when results comes, when the matching documents are displayed you don't get a &quot;preview&quot; of the document content with the matching key words. \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>And this is only with pdf documents. \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cimg src=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/66e74794