see correct count of files on sorting order also. \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;font-size:15px;\">\u003cbr> \u003c/div> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;font-size:15px;\">\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;\">\u003cfont face=\"Times New Roman\" size=3 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Note - I raised this ticket after discussing it with\u003cspan>&nbsp;\u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,7dd6744d-0b46-67bd-adbe-68611c21ddbd\">@Lodhari, Alpesh K. (Operations &amp; Technology)\u003c/a> \u003c/span>. As, in the modernized Azure instance, we currently don't have a setup for non-obfuscated database backups.\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003c/font> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;\">\u003cfont face=\"Times New Roman\" size=3 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">So, created this bug for further investigation.\u003c/font> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-size:14px;\">\u003cfont face=\"Times New Roman\" size=3 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Let me know if anything is required on this to investigate further.\u003c/font> \u003c/div>\u003cbr>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"iSheet","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916522","tests":[]},{"id":916666,"title":"Workflow Rule Email Font Size Not Reflected in Original Email","state":"Approved","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\SWAT","areaShort":"SWAT","issueSource":"Production","createdDate":"2026-04-01","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cspan>\u003cspan style=\"font-family:-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, system-ui, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Web&quot;, sans-serif;\">\u003cp>In the workflow rule email action, when a specific font size is configured, the same font size is not reflected in the original email content. \u003c/p>\u003cp>This behavior has been verified in two instances: \u003cstrong>betademo (legacy)\u003c/strong> and \u003cstrong>supportmodern (mod)\u003c/strong>.&nbsp;\u003cbr>\u003cbr>\nWhen the email is received in Outlook, and the \u003cstrong>Forward\u003c/strong> option is clicked, a small \u003cstrong>CK editor panel\u003c/strong> is displayed, where the font size is verified and found not to match the configured size from the workflow rule. \u003c/p>\u003cp>We have already discussed with \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,13cb893c-4f4b-67e6-af06-659b4281ffe4\">@Kishor, Kundan (TR Technology)\u003c/a>. For any issue, replication-related query, please contact him. \u003c/p>&nbsp;\u003c/span>\u003c/span>\u003cspan>\u003cspan style=\"font-family:-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, system-ui, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Web&quot;, sans-serif;\">\u003cp>\u003cbr> \u003c/p>&nbsp;\u003c/span>\u003c/span>\u003c/span>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Workflow / Rules","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916666","tests":[]},{"id":916705,"title":"File module with DMD view : System error while open document having quick search applied","state":"Approved","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\SWAT","areaShort":"SWAT","issueSource":"Production","createdDate":"2026-04-01","description":"\u003cdiv>Client got the&nbsp;\u003cspan style=\"display:inline !important;\">System error while open document having quick search applied. Without quick search, no system error presented.\u003c/span> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>Video is available in the related TSI ticket but can be easily replicated with the steps mentioned. \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>RCA found with help from AI,&nbsp;Griffin_getDocumentIDCSVForMetaDataSheet SP has&nbsp;@p_filterTextValue parameter with NVARCHAR(500) limit. When you try to search with few sample words, the XML generated at Java side exceeds the limit of 500 characters. \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>Solution is to change it to&nbsp;\u003cspan style=\"display:inline !important;\">NVARCHAR(MAX) as the inner SP also have same declaration for this parameter. Please let me know if any questions. Also its day 1 issue based on the file history.&nbsp;\u003c/span> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Search / Indexing","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916705","tests":[]},{"id":916731,"title":"Native office(Webdav) not working for any Excel files","state":"Approved","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\SWAT","areaShort":"SWAT","issueSource":"Production","createdDate":"2026-04-01","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cb>Issue description\u003c/b> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv>\u003cb>\u003cdiv style=\"font-family:'Segoe UI';font-weight:400;\">\u003cul>\u003cli>When customers open an Excel file in \u003cstrong>Edit mode\u003c/strong> using \u003cstrong>Microsoft Office (Native or WebDAV)\u003c/strong>, add some content, and try to save the file, they encounter an error.\u003cimg src=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/66e74794-9916-410b-b624-07d49748bbff/_apis/wit/attachments/263c48c1-f99a-40be-ad8c-6bf1d77a2862?fileName=image.png\" alt=Image> \u003c/li>\u003cli>I have tested this scenario across multiple data centers (ZUS1, SG1, DEU1, and ZUK1) and was able to reproduce the issue in all of them. However, when attempting to replicate the same issue on our test instance (isheetrelleg1), the problem does not occur. \u003c/li>\u003cul>\u003cli>Tested instances&nbsp; \u003c/li>\u003cul>\u003cli>\u003ca href=\"https://aacounty.highq.com/aacounty/getCBV.action\" target=_blank rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://aacounty.highq.com/aacounty/getCBV.action\u003c/a> \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003ca href=\"https://authoritybrands.highq.com/authoritybrands/getCBV.action\" target=_blank rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://authoritybrands.highq.com/authoritybrands/getCBV.action\u003c/a> \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003ca href=\"https://betademo.highq.com/betademo/getCBV.action\" target=_blank rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://betademo.highq.com/betademo/getCBV.action\u003c/a> \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003ca href=\"https://supportuatv4.highq.com/supportuatvfour/\" target=_blank rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://supportuatv4.highq.com/supportuatvfour/\u003c/a> \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003ca href=\"https://collaborate.highq.com/sitepoint/getCBV.action\" target=_blank rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://collaborate.highq.com/sitepoint/getCBV.action\u003c/a>\u003cbr> \u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003ca href=\"https://teamup.kromannreumert.com/kromannreumert/getCBV.action\" target=_blank rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://teamup.kromannreumert.com/kromannreumert/getCBV.action\u003c/a>\u003cbr> \u003c/li> \u003c/ul> \u003c/ul>\u003cli>This indicates a potential issue specific to the production (live) environments across all data centers. Since this functionality is currently blocked from the customer’s perspective, I am raising this as a P2 issue. \u003c/li>\u003cli>We have already discussed this during our daily catch‑up meeting with \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,58183e74-21f7-6f22-abfb-2788c26aab8d\">@Trivedi, Kinjal (TR Technology)\u003c/a> . For any questions or additional details, please feel free to reach out to \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,58183e74-21f7-6f22-abfb-2788c26aab8d\">@Trivedi, Kinjal (TR Technology)\u003c/a> , or me. \u003c/li> \u003c/ul>\u003cdiv>CC: \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,7dd6744d-0b46-67bd-adbe-68611c21ddbd\">@Lodhari, Alpesh K. (Operations &amp; Technology)\u003c/a>&nbsp;/ \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,4a190675-2be9-6112-9938-8fe5503c4d95\">@Xiong, Nhia (Operations &amp; Technology)\u003c/a> \u003c/div>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003cbr>\u003c/b> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Files / Documents","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916731","tests":[]},{"id":916834,"title":"Investigation  