tion Mono&quot;, Courier, monospace;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgba(28, 43, 52, 0.98);font-size:13px;text-align:left;background-color:rgba(88, 95, 112, 0.05);display:inline !important;\">\u003cspan>&nbsp;\u003c/span>messages lost.\u003c/span>\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cimg src=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/66e74794-9916-410b-b624-07d49748bbff/_apis/wit/attachments/aa04cf02-336a-4233-b650-82f9120aa645?fileName=image.png\" alt=Image style=\"box-sizing:border-box;max-width:100%;align-self:center;\">\u003cbr> \u003c/div>\u003c/span>\u003c/span>\u003cdiv>OBF DB Backup :&nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://trenterprise.service-now.com/sc_req_item.do?sys_id=b2e172e42f840fd05c6b354fafa4e354&amp;sysparm_record_target=sc_req_item&amp;sysparm_record_row=1&amp;sysparm_record_rows=1&amp;sysparm_record_list=request%3Df6e172e42f840fd05c6b354fafa4e353%5eORDERBYDESCnumber\" target=_blank rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://trenterprise.service-now.com/sc_req_item.do?sys_id=b2e172e42f840fd05c6b354fafa4e354&amp;sysparm_record_target=sc_req_item&amp;sysparm_record_row=1&amp;sysparm_record_rows=1&amp;sysparm_record_list=request%3Df6e172e42f840fd05c6b354fafa4e353%5eORDERBYDESCnumber\u003c/a>&nbsp;\u003cbr>\u003cbr>I discussed this with \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,58183e74-21f7-6f22-abfb-2788c26aab8d\">@Trivedi, Kinjal (TR Technology)\u003c/a> . We have seen a similar (older) ticket for this behaviour, which was marked as fixed in version \u003cstrong>5.9.23.1\u003c/strong>. The test case on that ticket confirms that adding/removing users from groups was validated. \u003c/div>\u003cp style=\"margin-bottom:16px;margin-left:0;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>\u003cb>BUG\u003c/b> ticket : \u003ca href=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/907306/\" data-vss-mention=\"version:1.0\">#907306\u003c/a>&nbsp;(5.9.23.1)\u003cbr> \u003cp> \u003c/p>\u003cp style=\"margin-bottom:16px;margin-left:0;margin-top:0px;\">\u003cspan>\u003cb>TestCase BUG ticket :\u003c/b>&nbsp;\u003cspan style=\"display:inline !important;\">\u003cspan style=\"display:inline !important;\">\u003ca href=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/907306#14677030\">https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/907306#14677030\u003c/a>\u003cbr>\u003c/span>\u003c/span>\u003cbr>However, when I reviewed the \u003cstrong>same log \u003ca href=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/902570#14644192\">links \u003c/a>&nbsp;referenced in the BUG ticket\u003c/strong>, I am still seeing the same error patterns for this customer. \u003cbr>\u003cb>NOTE \u003c/b>: \u003ci>I also discussed this with \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,7dd6744d-0b46-67bd-adbe-68611c21ddbd\">@Lodhari, Alpesh K. (Operations &amp; Technology)\u003c/a>&nbsp; and \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,58183e74-21f7-6f22-abfb-2788c26aab8d\">@Trivedi, Kinjal (TR Technology)\u003c/a> , and based on these findings I am raising a \u003cstrong>new bug ticket\u003c/strong> to investigate further for this specific client and scenario.\u003c/i>\u003cbr>\u003cbr>\u003c/span> \u003c/p>\u003cdiv>REF ADO : \u003ca href=\"https://tr-legal.visualstudio.com/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916701/\" data-vss-mention=\"version:1.0\">#916701\u003c/a>&nbsp; \u003c/div>","functionality":"Infrastructure / Deployment","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916834","tests":[]},{"id":916874,"title":"iSheet Workflow Rule Evaluates Number Column Change on Update Event Without Data Difference","state":"Active","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\SWAT","areaShort":"SWAT","issueSource":"Production","createdDate":"2026-04-02","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cspan>\u003cp>The client has configured a workflow rule based on an \u003cstrong>iSheet record update\u003c/strong>, with the condition \u003cstrong>“Number column changes”\u003c/strong> and a corresponding action. \u003c/p>\u003cp>When a new iSheet record is added to the relevant sheet and the same record is later edited and saved \u003cstrong>without making any changes\u003c/strong>, the rule condition is still satisfied, and the workflow is executed—even though no change was made to the \u003cstrong>Number\u003c/strong> column. \u003c/p>\u003cp>This behavior indicates that the rule is triggered on record save rather than detecting an actual value change in the Number column. \u003c/p>\u003cp>We were able to replicate this issue in the \u003cstrong>modisheetauto2\u003c/strong> instance. This issue has already been discussed with \u003cstrong>\u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,58183e74-21f7-6f22-abfb-2788c26aab8d\">@Trivedi, Kinjal (TR Technology)\u003c/a> \u003c/strong>. \u003c/p>\u003cp>\u003cbr> \u003c/p>\u003cp>CC: \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,7dd6744d-0b46-67bd-adbe-68611c21ddbd\">@Lodhari, Alpesh K. (Operations &amp; Technology)\u003c/a>&nbsp;/ \u003ca href=\"#\" data-vss-mention=\"version:2.0,4a190675-2be9-6112-9938-8fe5503c4d95\">@Xiong, Nhia (Operations &amp; Technology)\u003c/a> \u003c/p>\u003c/span>\u003cbr> \u003c/div>","functionality":"Workflow / Rules","url":"https://dev.azure.com/tr-legal/HighQ%20Tech/_workitems/edit/916874","tests":[]},{"id":916887,"title":"913600 - Incorrect amount displayed in chart","state":"Approved","areaPath":"HighQ Tech\\SWAT","areaShort":"SWAT","issueSource":"Production","createdDate":"2026-04-02","description":"\u003cdiv>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Hello Team, \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">The client reached out regarding an incorrect display on the chart. \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003cbr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"> \u003c/div>\u003cdiv style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">\u003ca href=\"https://clients.taylorwessing.com/t